                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm pretty sure that summoned pets don't get any exp unless they do 100% of the damage.  (i.e. if you do at least 5 points of damage, the summoned pets get nothing)
<br />

<br />
However, charmed pets do take experience, based on how much of the damage they did.  (Which, means that in a high dps group, charmed pets take less exp). I believe there is a cutoff for this, but I don't remember what it is.
<br />

<br />
What I haven't tested, however, is how 3-4 charmed pets in a group take exp.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tashim</a>, 65th Enchanter
<br />
<a href="http://www.drow.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a>
