<br />
-Tomar</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Just from what I remember (this could be different now, as I haven't really been playing much for the last few months).  Enchaters actually have 3 different exp charts depending on which pet we use. 
<br />

<br />
Animation is just like any other summoned pet, 1 pt of group dmg and they get no exp. 
<br />

<br />
Normal charms get 75% of the exp if they do all the dmg, if you do one point  they get 33% and it slides from there based on pet vs group dmg.
<br />

<br />
DC pets are what hurt us exp wise - 75% if no group damage, 50% sliding scale based on group dmg. (numbers could be off here).
<br />

<br />
I won't call this gospel but I know summoned, charmed and DC are all on different exp scales.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
